	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=16689><span id=Scholar>Badger</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>62 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I found a great area to practice Safe Fall, the canyon in East Karana leading to Highpass. Just go up the sloping trail and jump off. As it gets easier, keep going further up the slope. The trick is to walk off the trail backwards and fall facing the wall. I went from 40 to 75 in less than an hour (I was jumping off at -3192 x -4277 when I finally maxed out)and took minimal damage.<br><br>Just keep an eye and ear open for any passing mobs (although the only thing that came by while I was there besides a couple of PCs was a carrion spider).<br><br>Garren Ravenclaw <br>Monk of the 14th Season <br>Silent Fist Clan <br>Morelle-Thule </p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
