	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Apr 12th 1:31 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=38862><span id= >GysmoSan</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have come up with a neat trick for soloing these 3 frogloks. They are anoying because they run away and can swim damn fast...<br><br>When they are blue to you,<br>1) Attack one of them until it runs away. Let it run.<br>2) Stand with your back to the wall, to the right of their lair, looking down the corridor and TURN OFF your attack.<br>3) The Froglok invariably comes down the coridor and since you stopped attacking you can now kick and attack straight away, with any luck duel weilding for another blow.<br>4) This time follow it and it always goes the same way past the bank entrance and gets stuck at a relative dead end. While following it turn off attack again.<br>5) When you catch up to it, kick and attack and then turn away so it doesn't run back down the corridor. Turn back and attack again. Keep doing this until they die :-) If you need air its straight up from here....<br><br>I hope this is usefull.. Now all you have to do is spend hours killing these Frogloks until they wise up and hand over a nice pair of gloves :-)</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
