	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>201 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>My advice on the armor since you are Iksar is save your plat for cured silk.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the meantime go to the haggle baron directly across from the monk guild and /hail Klok Mugruk.  Follow the dialogue string and he will give you a quest for curscale armor.  This stuff is pretty much the same as raw silk, maybe even a bit better due to some of the extra bonuses you get (save vs. poison and such) and best of all it's FREE.  So, in the meantime you can save up whatever plat you can scrape and begin buying cured silk piece by piece.<br><br>One final note, if you kill spiders collect the silks and start combining them two at a time to make silk swatches.  Lots of tailors will give you discounts on armor if you hand them a stack of these bad boys.  <br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Zasshatiz - 22 Iksar Monk<br>Circle of Radiance Guild<br>Luclin Server</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
