<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98666949642678>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=98666949642678>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98666949642678>RE: low level monk</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98666949642678#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Apr 7th 2:51 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=9543><span id=Scholar>Landrion</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>35 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You are pretty much stuck with cloth until you can afford to buy raw silk and then cured silk.<br><br>Raw silk is made by players using the tailoring skill with spider silks, weighs about 0.4 per piece, and is also worn by casters.<br><br>Cured silk is made by players with the tailoring skill and brewing skill (one of the ingredients is Heady Kiola).&nbsp;&nbsp;It is also made with spider silks.  It is great for monks because it is very light (0.1 per item) and has ac the same as leather, and only monks can wear it.<br><br>You also could start practicing tailoring and brewing to make your own cured silk.  It will take a while because it is a fairly high difficulty item to make (skill level 65 is when it's trivial i think).<br><br>Although you can buy and wear leather, I would not recommend it, because a full set of leather would bring your weight limit above the 14 ideal for monks.<br><br>Cured silk usually sells for about 1 to 2 pp per ac, so a chest piece will sell for 8 to 16 pp.  Also, cured gives you the look that the monk trainers have.<br><br>Hope that helps :)<br><br>Zzaarno Painmaker<br>22 monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
