	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=9543><span id=Scholar>Landrion</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>35 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Monks get double attack at level 15.&nbsp;&nbsp;This will give you the CHANCE to hit up to 4 times in one round provided you are dual wielding (no shield or torch in one hand, and no 2hb weapon).  The higher your dual wield and double attack skills get, the more often you will hit 2, 3 or 4 times in a round.<br><br>As a related note, double attack goes up pretty quickly on its own, so don't waste training points on it.  Just train 1 point so you get the skill, then let it go up as you fight.  Use your training points for harder to build skills like mend, feign death, or your special attacks.<br><br>Zzaarno Painmaker<br>23 Iksar Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells<br><br>(corrected and updated 4/8/01)</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
