	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>201 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>YES, it is possible to raise both skills by having one in the primary and one in the secondary, HOWEVER (there's always a however, heheh) how quickly your off-hand advances depends on your dual weild skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;So, until your DW skill gets reasonably high (I don't know, maybe 60 or so, any other figures out there) you're going to see your primary advancing a lot and your secondary barely creeping.<br><br>Solution:  alternate.  Get your 1HB up to a certain level, then switch so your club is in your left hand, rinse and repeat (a fond saying on this board I'm noticing).<br><br>2HB, that's another monster.  Unfortunately one I've put off until now.  I'm dreading the day ...<br><br>Zasshatiz - 17 Iksar Monk<br>Gluadilae - 19 Wood Elf Ranger<br>Luclin Server</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
